We were fooled by the good reviews. Never again. Food was definitely not good. Sushi rice was old/dry and the fish itself was fishy. We ordered 4 rolls - all tasted old. The Kani salad was flavorless, 99% cucumber, and included a huge piece of iceberg lettuce at the bottom to make it look like you were getting a decent portion. Bubble teas were flavorless/super watered down and we ended up tossing them. The only decent thing was the edamame. Other than that is was a HUGE waste of money, will not order again.

This is arguably the worst sushi I’ve ever ordered. I just got one of the sushi bowls and the bowl is full of rice (not on the menu nor in the picture, I don’t eat rice & would not have ordered this had I known the bowl was mostly rice) and hard white iceberg lettuce. The nine pieces of fish were small, the avocado hard and inedible and the egg is simply disgusting. I would give 0 stars if I could. I might as well have opened my window and thrown my money out. The only good part of this experience was that the food came fast via Ubereats. Never again, just yuck.
